<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Engine Electrical - Electronic
        Control Module (ECM)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="5">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg6/eg6974.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Glow Plug Relay</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Glow Plug Connector Terminals</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Battery Connection Terminal</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery and glow plug connectors from glow plug relay.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure>
                <graphic filename="../figeg7/eg7410.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="592px" box="no"/>
                <caption>ECM Wiring Harnesses and Mounting Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Connector Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Wiring Harness</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">ECM Mounting Bolt (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a square head driver to unscrew the connector bolt. Disconnect the engine wiring
                    harness from the ECM.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the ECM from the support assembly, remove the four mounting bolts and lift the
                    ECM from the support bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the ECM and support assembly
                    <emph type="bold">as one unit</emph>, perform the following steps:
                </para>
                <figure id="f1201008" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg6/eg6970.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>ECM Support Assembly Lower Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two lower mounting bolts for the ECM support assembly.</para>
                    <figure id="f2051001" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figeg9/eg9138.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                                 box="yes"/>
                        <caption>ECM Support Assembly Upper Mounting Bolts</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two upper mounting bolts for the ECM support assembly.</para>
                    <figure id="f1201009" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../figeg6/eg6971.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                                 box="yes"/>
                        <caption>Bottom Mounting Bracket</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">Top Bushing</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">Bushing Pin</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">Bottom Bushing</callout1>
                            <callout1 type="arabic">Bottom Mounting Bracket</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If necessary, remove the bushings and pins from the mounting brackets.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
